narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: fundamental theorem of calculus, integration, differentiation, slope fields
I developed a further understanding on single variable calculus.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
strengths: the review sessions for the exams and peer tutor office hours were helpful 

weaknesses: the psets were often times lengthy and more complex than the exams and sometimes it wouldn't help me for the exam. When we had midterms, we also had psets that same week and it made it incredibly stressful to study for the exam
The strengths of this course is that it is designed in a way where material builds upon each other.

Oftentimes, our class felt behind other sections of the same course and we had to rely heavily on peer tutors to help us navigate the material. This class was taught at a very fast pace compared to what I have heard from other sections, and it felt as though the book was regurgitated to us each class. I felt that I had to teach the material to myself as opposed to having someone teach it to me.  Sometimes, the material had to be retaught to us from the tutors as it appeared concepts were presented to us incorrectly and at times, was just wrong. I don't think our instruction was particularly strong, however, I felt the problem sets were definitely helpful tools to see what I did and did not understand from class. I don't think we had enough time in class to engage with example problems that we would see on the assignments.
A lot of content towards the end.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: If they needed to take the class or if they liked math then yes! This class can be challenging so people should take that in mind.
Yes, it is a good way to review material from calculus, however, it may be more challenging for students with no calculus experience.
I would recommend this course to another student, but I feel like the instructor needs to alter the class to make it an environment conducive to better learning.
